🚀 I built a mental health platform that helps people anonymously.

Here's why:

3 months ago, I started building MindSpace - a full-stack mental health support platform. I wanted to create something that could actually help people.

What I built:

💬 Anonymous real-time chat support - Talk without revealing identity
📔 Mood journal with analytics - Track patterns over time
📋 PHQ-9 depression assessment - Clinically validated screening
🧘 Mindfulness tools - Breathing exercises & meditation
👨‍⚕️ Therapist directory - Find licensed professionals
🆘 24/7 crisis resources - One-click emergency support

Tech stack:
• Next.js 14 + Tailwind CSS
• Node.js + Express backend
• MongoDB Atlas for data
• Socket.io for real-time chat
• Deployed on Vercel + Render

The hardest part? WebSocket connection management across page navigation. Keeping the chat alive while users moved between pages was tricky, but I solved it with a global socket context.

The most rewarding part? Seeing real users benefit from anonymous support.

